{
  "_setup_instructions": [
    "HOW TO SET UP LINE MESSAGING API (takes about 10 minutes)",
    "",
    "STEP 1 — Create a LINE Official Account (free):",
    "  1. Go to https://developers.line.biz/console/",
    "  2. Log in with your personal LINE account",
    "  3. Click 'Create a new provider' → type any name (e.g. 'SET Alert') → Create",
    "  4. Click 'Create a new channel' → choose 'Messaging API'",
    "  5. Fill in: Channel name (e.g. 'SET Signal Bot'), description, category → Create",
    "",
    "STEP 2 — Get your Channel Access Token:",
    "  1. Inside your new channel, click the 'Messaging API' tab",
    "  2. Scroll to the bottom → 'Channel access token (long-lived)'",
    "  3. Click 'Issue' → copy the long token that appears",
    "  4. Paste it below into 'line_channel_access_token'",
    "",
    "STEP 3 — Get your LINE User ID:",
    "  1. Inside your channel, click the 'Basic settings' tab",
    "  2. Scroll down to find 'Your user ID' (starts with U, like Uabc123...)",
    "  3. Copy it and paste below into 'line_user_id'",
    "",
    "STEP 4 — Add your bot as a LINE friend (REQUIRED to receive messages):",
    "  1. In your channel, click the 'Messaging API' tab",
    "  2. Scan the QR code with your LINE app → Add as friend",
    "  3. Send any message to the bot (e.g. 'hello') — this activates the connection",
    "",
    "STEP 5 — Run the script to test:",
    "  python set_signal_alert.py",
    "",
    "FREE TIER NOTE: LINE Messaging API free plan includes 200 messages/month.",
    "This alert runs twice daily on weekdays = ~44 messages/month. Well within free limit."
  ],
